22/01/2007
MOSCOW, Russian Federation -- President Vladimir Putin reiterated on Sunday (January 21st) that Russia opposes any imposed solution to the Kosovo status problem. 
During a joint news conference with German Chancellor Angela Merkel after talks in the Russian town of Sochi, Putin said a solution for Kosovo can only function in the long term "if it is acceptable to both Belgrade and Pristina".
In other news Sunday, Kosovo marked the first anniversary of the death of former President Ibrahim Rugova. 
Representatives of the Kosovo interim institutions, political parties and UNMIK gathered in Pristina to commemorate Rugova, the founder and leader of the Democratic League of Kosovo. 
(Danas, Albanian News - 22/01/07; Tanjug, DPA, Beta, B92 - 21/01/07)
